The IEBC yesterday said the ODM primaries scheduled to begin today are illegal, as they are outside the set timelines.ODM plans to start primaries in Bungoma, Busia and Machakos today. Kisii, Nyamira, Samburu and Trans Nzoia will follow on Sunday. ODM nominations are scheduled to end on April 23. Independent Electoral and Boundaries Commission communication director Andrew Limo said parties can only hold primaries after the agency gazettes the list of aspirants.He said the IEBC will allow parties to conduct primaries from April 13 to 26 as per the Constitution.They are supposed to &ldquo;submit their list of nominees selected to contest the elections to the Commission on or before May 10&rdquo;, Limo said in a statement released yesterday to remind political parties of the set timelines.He said parties that directly select their nominees are required to submit the list of persons on or before May 10.&ldquo;Section 31 (2C) of the Election Act requires the Commission to publish the names of persons contesting in a party primary and the date of the party primary within seven days of the receipt of the names of the party candidates,&rdquo; the statement says. He added that the deadline for submitting the names was this past Wednesday.The commission is in the process of gazetting names of candidates submitted by political parties in accordance with the law, Limo said.&ldquo;Parties may proceed to hold their primaries in accordance with the commission&rsquo;s timelines once the candidates have been published in the Kenya Gazette,&rdquo; the statement reads. Opposition chief Raila Odinga has insisted parties are independent and as such cannot take orders from the commission on when to conduct their nominations.